    "body": "One of our primary goals is to avoid state reads whilst generating an attestation. To avoid this, we presently we only allow attesting for the current slot. However, this is too strict we could also expand it to include *some* prior slots.\r\n\r\nTo produce an attestation we need the following things from a `BeaconState`:\r\n\r\n1. **The beacon committee length**: easily available for prev/current/next epoch\r\n1. **The \"head\" root**: known for `SLOTS_PER_HISTORICAL_ROOT` (8,192) slots in the past via `state.block_roots`.\r\n1. **The \"source\" epoch/root**: `state.current_justified_epoch` gives us the current epoch, `state.previous_justified_epoch` gives us the previous epoch, next epoch is unknown.\r\n1. **The \"target\" epoch/root**: known for `SLOTS_PER_HISTORICAL_ROOT / 32` epochs in the past via `state.block_roots`.\r\n\r\nTherefore, given some `BeaconState` (the *head state* in our case) it is possible to produce an attestation in the current and previous epochs without doing any state reads.\r\n\r\nTo achieve this, I think we'll need to modify some of the logic here to read values for the previous epch:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/3a24ca5f14c6e6d6612fd43eca82aa0c1e6aba16/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/beacon_chain.rs#L961-L968\r\n\r\nAnd then loosen this constraint:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/3a24ca5f14c6e6d6612fd43eca82aa0c1e6aba16/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/beacon_chain.rs#L925-L950\r\n\r\n",
